    q: "What does scale-related repair cost?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $120, applied to repair. Steam generator descale alone $360-540. Water-level probe cleaning $200-280. Probe replacement (when scale damage is irreversible) $260-440. Heating element replacement (when scale insulation has shortened element life) $640-920. Combined heavy-duty descale + element + probe service can run $1,200-1,800. The cost equation favors prevention: scheduled quarterly descale at $400-500 is much cheaper than emergency element + probe replacement at $1,500+.",
  },
  {
    q: "What signs indicate my steamer has scale problems?",
    a: "Five symptoms ordered by severity. (1) Slow steam buildup or reduced steam output during operation: scale insulation on heating element. (2) Water-level alarm or controller misreading water level: scale on probes. (3) Steamer fills slowly or refuses to fill: scale-clogged inlet valve. (4) Visible white or grey deposits on element when service door is open: late-stage scale buildup. (5) Heating element open circuit (full failure): scale-induced overheating eventually burns out the element. Symptoms 1-3 indicate descale needed; symptom 5 means descale + element replacement.",
  },
  {
    q: "Do you do annual or quarterly steamer PM contracts?",
    a: "Yes. Quarterly PM (typical for LA institutional) covers descale + probe inspection + heating element visual + inlet valve check + door gasket inspection + drain valve service. Annual PM (typical for low-duty operations or operations with water softeners installed) covers the same scope at lower frequency. We document each visit appropriately for HACCP records and California Title 8 occupational safety compliance. Quote-based depending on the number of steamers, brand mix, and water-softener status.",
  },
];

